A Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) officer is in a
critical but stable condition following a shootout on Friday evening. According to Senior
Superintendent Wayne Minnaar, the shootout occurred when the police traced a
stolen van to Hillbrow, Johannesburg. "JMPD K9 officers received
information on the location of the van, in Hillbrow, which was hijacked. "When officers tried to
stop the van, a shootout ensued," Minnaar said. The JMPD officer was rushed to
Milpark Hospital. One suspect died and another
was arrested. 